metadata.name: R√™ve em Nuvens #5
metadata.description:
Even though sometimes our horizon seems to be obscured by problems and difficulties, the weather is always clear above the clouds.

"R√™ves em Nuvens", a mixture of French and Portuguese words meaning "Dreams in the clouds", is intended to be a message of hope and encouragement for all those who, at some point, have seen their perspectives disappear. They are still there, the stars and the sky are only hidden behind clouds.

Born from a two-month collaboration between Omar Lobato and Estienne, "R√™ve em Nuvens" uses noise assemblages to reproduce a cloudy sky, sometimes at night under a full moon, during a late afternoon or a sunny day. 

The colors, shape, texture and turbulence of the clouds are all variations that will give this series a style that can be both realistic and fantastic.

Although the parameters are attached to the hash of each edition, certain options are offered in order to be able to generate the image in the style that suits you best, whether for display on screen, or for printing:

Press the [1] key to toggle the noise effect
Press the [2] key to toggle the stucco texture
Press the [3] key to toggle the lines texture

Press the [S] key to save a 4K image in PNG format

Add "?size=xxx" at the end of the url to generate an image of xxx pixels

Authors: Omar Lobato & Estienne
May 2022

metadata.name: Phantoms #163
metadata.description:
Phantoms is a series of hazy memories of distant places. Some tranquil, others sinister, each scene is as much defined by what is revealed as by what remains unseen.

In this collection I aim to juxtapose hard and soft. Blocky shapes form the core of the compositions. Upon these surfaces, soft textures appear to flow and drip over the sides. Varying levels of opacity, lighting, and fog effects further soften the scenes to create an atmospheric, dream-like quality. By remaining semi-abstract, each of the color palettes are given the space to influence the mood dramatically.

Anagram #134
metadata.description:
'Anagram' explores the collision of nature with the modern world. Organic textures are generated within geometric boundaries to create a system of unique 'letters' that are combined and rearranged form a composition. Thirty-one texture types are possible, designed to work in five environments. Uncommon 'Assimilate' versions pull from the full texture set to represent the source 'word' of the generated Anagrams.

metadata.description:
In celebration of #tezos4tezos I am releasing this mini version of a more complex work in progress. 

Every 24th mint (ex: 1, 24, 48, 72, etc) will receive a free physical woodcut.
https://alleditions.art/p/miniglyph

This project is designed such that it can export a layered vector SVG that can be used for plotting or cutting out of wood with a laser or paper with a Cricut.

Shift P - Export a PNG
Shift S - Export an SVG
Shift E - explode the layers

metadata.name: Geode #32
metadata.description:
A single seed shape is chosen from 13, and placed onto the plane. At every step, a copy of this seed is laid edge-to-edge adjacent to an existing shape, without causing any overlaps. This copy is colored based on the edge it shares with the existing shape. The process continues until the animation completes.

New shapes are placed closest to a moving target. In some mints, this target is slow moving, causing new shapes to expand radially from the seed. In other mints, this target races around, causing new shapes to chase it. 

Each of the 13 shapes forms different patterns under different circumstances. Not all patterns will be explored.

Controls:
  - SPACE: Pause/unpause the animation.
  - ENTER: Skip the animation.
  - R: Restart the animation.

URL Params:
  - "preview=1": Skip the animation.
  - "flex=1": Adapt the boundaries to the size of the window.
  - ‚Äúslow=1‚Äù: Draw only one shape per frame.
